Where is it coming from?

261
00:14:25,199 --> 00:14:26,467
( Gasps )

262
00:14:30,871 --> 00:14:32,539
( Grunting )

263
00:14:32,573 --> 00:14:35,176
Where am I?

264
00:14:35,209 --> 00:14:36,477
Netero: All right...

265
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:38,545
( Ladybug ant gasps )

266
00:14:38,579 --> 00:14:42,950
Netero: Let’s get this started,
shall we?

267
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:45,385
Colt: What?

268
00:14:45,419 --> 00:14:47,254
Chiona’s squadron is missing?

269
00:14:47,287 --> 00:14:48,989
Peggy: That’s right.

270
00:14:49,022 --> 00:14:51,525
Colt: And was it the same way
that reikei’s disappeared?

271
00:14:51,558 --> 00:14:52,959
Peggy: Yes, it appears so.

272
00:14:52,993 --> 00:14:55,162
The leader went missing first.

273
00:14:55,195 --> 00:14:58,165
Then the rest of them
vanished one by one.

274
00:14:58,198 --> 00:14:59,566
Colt: Hmm.

275
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:02,002
Peggy: Are the humans
fighting back?

276
00:15:02,035 --> 00:15:05,605
Colt: It seems that that is
the most logical conclusion.

277
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:09,276
Because of this filtering,
there are fewer of us,

278
00:15:09,309 --> 00:15:12,179
and the food
is scattering farther away.

279
00:15:12,212 --> 00:15:14,948
If humans target us
in a long hunt,

280
00:15:14,982 --> 00:15:17,651
it could mean trouble
for us and a lot.

281
00:15:17,684 --> 00:15:19,452
Peggy: Then wouldn’t it be wise

282
00:15:19,486 --> 00:15:22,055
to ask the queen
to move to the castle?

283
00:15:22,089 --> 00:15:24,224
Colt: Of course not.
In her current condition,

284
00:15:24,258 --> 00:15:26,594
we should avoid troubling her
at all cost.

285
00:15:26,627 --> 00:15:28,195
Peggy: Well, then perhaps

286
00:15:28,228 --> 00:15:30,931
we should consult
lord neferpitou instead.

287
00:15:30,964 --> 00:15:32,265
( Sighs )

288
00:15:32,299 --> 00:15:34,635
Though that idea
doesn’t thrill me at all.

289
00:15:34,668 --> 00:15:36,670
( Machinery humming )

290
00:15:38,272 --> 00:15:40,274
( Liquid bubbling )

291
00:15:43,377 --> 00:15:45,613
Neferpitou:
I leave the outside to you.

292
00:15:45,646 --> 00:15:49,216
We’ll just focus
on defending the fortress.

293
00:15:49,249 --> 00:15:53,286
Mm. Needs to be
more concentrated, I think.

294
00:15:54,288 --> 00:15:56,023
♪

295
00:15:56,056 --> 00:15:57,658
Peggy: Just as expected.

296
00:15:57,691 --> 00:15:59,626
Colt: Well, this is better

297
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:02,596
than getting erratic orders,
I suppose.

298
00:16:02,629 --> 00:16:05,665
We should begin by determining
our current troop strength.

299
00:16:05,699 --> 00:16:07,534
How many squadron leaders?

300
00:16:07,568 --> 00:16:12,173
Peggy: Assuming chiona
was taken out, 28 remain.

301
00:16:14,441 --> 00:16:16,743
Colt: Each squadron leader
has four officers

302
00:16:16,777 --> 00:16:19,213
and, in some cases, five,

303
00:16:19,246 --> 00:16:20,781
and each officer in turn

304
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:24,318
commands ten to 15
low-level soldiers.

305
00:16:24,351 --> 00:16:27,087
Peggy: Some squadrons
are under tight control

306
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,122
and operate as intended,

307
00:16:29,156 --> 00:16:32,526
but there are many others
who do just as they please.

308
00:16:32,559 --> 00:16:35,562
Colt: And the four squadrons
that are missing

309
00:16:35,596 --> 00:16:38,065
fall under the latter category?

310
00:16:38,098 --> 00:16:39,132
Peggy: Of course.

311
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:40,634
Colt: Of the remaining,

312
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:43,670
over half of the squads
lack discipline.

313
00:16:43,704 --> 00:16:46,574
I highly doubt that they
would listen to advice.

314
00:16:46,607 --> 00:16:48,142
Peggy: Hmm.

315
00:16:48,175 --> 00:16:51,178
Ever since they discovered
how to control nen,

316
00:16:51,211 --> 00:16:53,080
they have become quite arrogant.

317
00:16:53,113 --> 00:16:57,384
Colt: I know, so let them
be bait while we set the trap.

318
00:16:59,353 --> 00:17:02,256
Netero: If you ask me,
i’d say that’s the strategy

319
00:17:02,289 --> 00:17:04,124
they’ve come up with by now.

320
00:17:04,158 --> 00:17:07,528
Morel: Well, we should be able
to keep the current plan then.

321
00:17:07,561 --> 00:17:09,096
Knov: Right.

322
00:17:09,129 --> 00:17:11,498
Morel: Just leave it
to knov and me.

323
00:17:11,532 --> 00:17:14,168
We’ll separate the bait
from the traps, easy.

324
00:17:14,201 --> 00:17:16,570
Knov: Actually I think
it might be good

325
00:17:16,603 --> 00:17:18,672
to tangle with a trap
every once in a while.

326
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:20,340
Morel: Huh?

327
00:17:20,374 --> 00:17:23,611
Knov: If we opt to leave
the organized troops for later,

328
00:17:23,644 --> 00:17:27,148
they might team up
and cause problems.

329
00:17:27,181 --> 00:17:30,151
I’d wager that soon
the organized and lax troops

330
00:17:30,184 --> 00:17:33,287
will probably start
pairing off from now on.

331
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:34,454
Netero: True.

332
00:17:34,488 --> 00:17:36,457
Knov: If we were to launch

333
00:17:36,490 --> 00:17:38,726
a completely
indiscriminate attack,

334
00:17:38,759 --> 00:17:41,462
we could create
as much chaos as possible.

335
00:17:41,495 --> 00:17:43,797
If all goes well,

336
00:17:43,831 --> 00:17:46,267
we’ll eliminate
another three or four squads

337
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,769
before they can update
their strategy.

338
00:17:48,802 --> 00:17:50,304
( Netero grunts )

339
00:17:50,337 --> 00:17:53,740
Knov: We can already anticipate
their next move.

340
00:17:53,774 --> 00:17:56,477
Barring
any unforeseen circumstances,

341
00:17:56,510 --> 00:18:00,247
we’ll finish up
before reinforcements arrive.

342
00:18:01,281 --> 00:18:03,083
Netero: I hope...

343
00:18:04,384 --> 00:18:06,019
Things go that way.

344
00:18:13,327 --> 00:18:14,495
Bisky: Three hours!

345
00:18:14,528 --> 00:18:15,796
Good! All done!

346
00:18:15,829 --> 00:18:20,000
( Boys panting )

347
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:22,536
Bisky: Okay! Now go and get him!

348
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:29,075
Knuckle: Here.

349
00:18:30,677 --> 00:18:31,811
( Dogs whimpering )

350
00:18:31,845 --> 00:18:33,046
Eh?

351
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:35,349
There are more of you guys
than I realized!

352
00:18:35,382 --> 00:18:37,951
Well, don’t hold back.
Go on and eat, too.

353
00:18:37,985 --> 00:18:39,019
( Dog barks )

354
00:18:39,052 --> 00:18:40,453
( Knuckle chuckles )

355
00:18:42,089 --> 00:18:44,858
( Chuckles )

356
00:18:44,892 --> 00:18:46,060
( Grunts )

357
00:18:46,093 --> 00:18:48,095
♪

358
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:54,668
They came back.

359
00:19:12,486 --> 00:19:14,688
Gon: Hey, knuckle, it’s on!

360
00:19:14,721 --> 00:19:16,957
Knuckle: Right!
Then bring it on!

361
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,992
I can take on
both of you at once!

362
00:19:19,026 --> 00:19:21,128
Killua: You think
you’re better than us,

363
00:19:21,161 --> 00:19:22,996
but I don’t give a damn!

364
00:19:23,030 --> 00:19:25,866
We’re still
more than happy to accept!

365
00:19:27,034 --> 00:19:28,469
Gon: Come on, killua!

366
00:19:28,502 --> 00:19:29,670
Killua: All right!

367
00:19:29,703 --> 00:19:32,072
( Both yelling )

368
00:19:34,575 --> 00:19:37,044
♪

369
00:19:48,088 --> 00:19:49,623
( Gon gasps )

370
00:19:49,656 --> 00:19:51,024
Whah!

371
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:55,595
Knuckle: Give me a break.

372
00:19:55,629 --> 00:19:57,731
I could keep playing
with you kids,

373
00:19:57,764 --> 00:20:00,600
but I just don’t have
that kind of time.

374
00:20:01,635 --> 00:20:03,203
Killua: Except that you do.

375
00:20:03,237 --> 00:20:06,640
Knuckle: So get serious!

376
00:20:06,673 --> 00:20:09,242
( Gon yells )

377
00:20:09,276 --> 00:20:11,211
Knuckle: Now that’s
more like it!

378
00:20:11,245 --> 00:20:13,280
Hah!

379
00:20:15,282 --> 00:20:17,651
Their bodies are worn out.

380
00:20:17,684 --> 00:20:22,055
All that’s moving them now
is sheer willpower.

381
00:20:22,089 --> 00:20:24,825
Once they’ve accomplished
the task at hand,

382
00:20:24,858 --> 00:20:26,059
their renewed confidence

383
00:20:26,093 --> 00:20:30,664
will allow them
to improve exponentially.

384
00:20:30,697 --> 00:20:34,701
However, if they
complete their mission,

385
00:20:34,735 --> 00:20:36,637
that means they’ll defeat me!

386
00:20:39,306 --> 00:20:41,341
That ain’t gonna happen!

387
00:20:50,117 --> 00:20:54,922
Oh, come on!
Is that really all you’ve got?!

388
00:20:54,955 --> 00:20:57,124
Shoot: Given his personality,

389
00:20:57,157 --> 00:21:01,261
it’s safe to assume
that he’s already been won over.

390
00:21:03,664 --> 00:21:06,233
I doubt he would
knowingly sell me out,

391
00:21:06,266 --> 00:21:10,070
but I can’t exactly trust him
to hold his tongue, either.

392
00:21:12,239 --> 00:21:15,976
My opportunity will be
on their way home.

393
00:21:16,009 --> 00:21:18,011
♪

394
00:21:19,213 --> 00:21:23,184
I will defeat them.

395
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:27,988
♪

396
00:21:28,021 --> 00:21:30,023
( Singing in Japanese )

